trend_summary: Throughout the series, the area keeps its low-rise suburban pattern but shows steady infill. New houses, small retail blocks and parking appear along the main east-west arterial, while a few former industrial lots are replaced by commercial or residential uses. Tree cover thickens overall, reflecting street-tree growth and local greening programs.
notable_changes: Progressive infill housing on vacant residential lots, especially south of the arterial.
Expansion of commercial plazas and parking near key junctions on the east-west corridor.
Redevelopment of a small industrial pocket into mixed commercial/residential blocks.
New local road stubs and cul-de-sacs connecting previously dead-end streets.
Increase in tree canopy and landscaped areas across neighbourhoods.
